page.title: 14HARRINGTON NEAR WORKINGTON
page.content: {Harrington}is a{small sea port}2.5 miles south of Workington on the Cumbrian coast. It has a large harbour which reflects that it was once an important port used for transporting coal and iron ore while{shipbuilding was the principle industry. The port today is used to harbour small pleasure craft and is no longer used for commercial purposes. Harrington's main{residential area is away from the harbour and many people who live there come from surrounding areas like Workington. The older houses of Harrington are situated on Church Road and there abouts.There are many public houses which reflects it's maritime past. Many of Harrington's industrial sites have been demolished and are now mainly{public open space.
